<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-11-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-11-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="110" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/411.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">King</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bangkok</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-11-28"><hi rend="italic">November 28,
                                    1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Siamese Government entirely indorse the Government of the United States’s
                            sympathy with Chinese Government in bereavement. Would not object
                            postponement Opium International Conference to 1st next February.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">King.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>